{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fileTest"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"filename","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">!, "},{"text":"test","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/FileTest","text":"FileTest","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib8FileTestV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apart from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isSymlink"},{"type":"text","text":" all tests follow symbolic links,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"so for a symbolic link to a regular file "},{"code":"g_file_test()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will return","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" for both ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isSymlink"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"isRegular","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note, that for a dangling symbolic link ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_file_test()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will return","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for ","type":"text"},{"code":"isSymlink","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":" for all other flags."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You should never use ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_file_test()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to test whether it is safe"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to perform an operation, because there is always the possibility"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the condition changing before you actually perform the operation,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"see "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, you might think you could use ","type":"text"},{"code":"isSymlink","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to know whether it is safe to write to a file without being","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tricked into writing into a different location. It doesn’t work!"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":[" \/\/ DON'T DO THIS"," if (!g_file_test (filename, G_FILE_TEST_IS_SYMLINK))","   {","     fd = g_open (filename, O_WRONLY);","     \/\/ write to fd","   }",""," \/\/ DO THIS INSTEAD"," fd = g_open (filename, O_WRONLY | O_NOFOLLOW | O_CLOEXEC);"," if (fd == -1)","   {","     \/\/ check error","     if (errno == ELOOP)","       \/\/ file is a symlink and can be ignored","     else","       \/\/ handle errors as before","   }"," else","   {","     \/\/ write to fd","   }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Another thing to note is that ","type":"text"},{"code":"exists","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isExecutable"},{"type":"text","text":" are implemented using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"access()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"system call. This usually doesn’t matter, but if your program"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is setuid or setgid it means that these tests will give you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the answer for the real user ID and group ID, rather than the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"effective user ID and group ID."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On Windows, there are no symlinks, so testing for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isSymlink"},{"type":"text","text":" will always return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":". Testing for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"isExecutable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will just check that the file exists and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"its name indicates that it is executable, checking for well-known"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"extensions and those listed in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"PATHEXT","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/fileTest(filename:test:)"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" if any of the tests in the bitfield ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"test"},{"text":" are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For example, ","type":"text"},{"code":"(G_FILE_TEST_EXISTS | G_FILE_TEST_IS_DIR)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if the file exists; the check whether it’s a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directory doesn’t matter since the existence test is "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". With","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the current set of available tests, there’s no point passing in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"more than one test at a time.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/filetest(filename:test:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"func","roleHeading":"Function","title":"fileTest(filename:test:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fileTest","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"filename","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">!, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"test"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib8FileTestV","text":"FileTest"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib8fileTest8filename4testSbSPys4Int8VGSg_AA04FileC0VtF"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/FileTest":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"FileTest"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/filetest","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"FileTest","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A test to perform on a file using "},{"code":"g_file_test()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"title":"FileTest","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/FileTest"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use":{"identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use","url":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TOCTOU"}],"type":"link","title":"TOCTOU"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/fileTest(filename:test:)":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/fileTest(filename:test:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if any of the tests in the bitfield "},{"code":"test","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". For example, "},{"code":"(G_FILE_TEST_EXISTS | G_FILE_TEST_IS_DIR)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" if the file exists; the check whether it’s a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"directory doesn’t matter since the existence test is "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". With","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the current set of available tests, there’s no point passing in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"more than one test at a time."}],"title":"fileTest(filename:test:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fileTest","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"filename"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"test","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib8FileTestV","text":"FileTest","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier",